# About lvgm / MSXgl

The `lvgm` library is a part of the MSXgl libraries. It only contains the necessary functions to play files in LVGM format.

This document provides information about the `MSXgl` software, which is a third-party package distributed with the `nmenu` project.

As stated in the main `contrib/README` file, `lvgm / MSXgl` is not part of `nmenu`. It is developed and maintained by its own authors and is distributed under its own license terms.

## Package: lvgm / MSXgl

* Description: MSXgl is a Game Library wrote in C and targeting MSX computers.
* Author(s): @aoineko-fr (https://github.com/aoineko-fr)
* Version: v1.2.4
* Original Source: https://github.com/aoineko-fr/MSXgl
* License: CC-BY-SA-4.0 license

## Documentation

For detailed information on using `lvgm`, including its features, options, and any dependencies, please refer to the original documentation provided by its authors. This documentation might be found at:

* The original source/homepage linked above.
* Files within the `lvgm` subdirectory (e.g., `lvgm/README.MD`, `lvgm/docs/`).

